70
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:32,840
Ah...

71
00:06:06,470 --> 00:06:07,470
Morning.

72
00:06:07,660 --> 00:06:08,660
Morning.

73
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,500
You've been up for a while?

74
00:06:10,860 --> 00:06:11,860
Yeah.

75
00:06:24,710 --> 00:06:26,300
Um, Shizuma.

76
00:06:28,310 --> 00:06:29,580
About our future...

77
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:31,520
I need some time to think.

78
00:06:36,210 --> 00:06:37,210
I want to...

79
00:06:38,350 --> 00:06:41,300
become someone who can properly return your feelings.

80
00:06:44,790 --> 00:06:45,790
Okay.

81
00:06:46,610 --> 00:06:47,610
I understand.

82
00:06:48,770 --> 00:06:49,770
I'll wait for you.

83
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:04,050
I had a good talk with Minato.

84
00:07:08,110 --> 00:07:09,610
That's a nice photo.

85
00:07:10,370 --> 00:07:11,370
It is.

86
00:07:13,110 --> 00:07:14,840
So, what about Minato-san?

87
00:07:17,550 --> 00:07:19,460
He said he needs time to think.

88
00:07:20,170 --> 00:07:21,170
Huh?

89
00:07:21,910 --> 00:07:23,110
He's still saying that?

90
00:07:24,490 --> 00:07:25,490
No, that's not it.

91
00:07:27,820 --> 00:07:29,810
He said he wants to properly return my feelings.

92
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:33,100
So he needs some time to think.

93
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:36,750
Minato said that?

94
00:07:38,030 --> 00:07:39,030
Yes.

95
00:07:41,410 --> 00:07:42,410
I see.

96
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:46,000
He's trying to move forward on his own.

97
00:07:47,020 --> 00:07:48,360
That's what I think too.

98
00:07:51,530 --> 00:07:52,730
