of the one you love, like I did.

119
00:09:06,290 --> 00:09:08,570
You're really something else in that regard.

120
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:10,910
Back when I was worried about my brother,

121
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:13,420
and told you all those nasty rumors,

122
00:09:14,050 --> 00:09:15,670
you weren't discouraged at all.

123
00:09:17,530 --> 00:09:18,530
Oh, right.

124
00:09:21,590 --> 00:09:23,700
You're not like me. You're strong.

125
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:27,310
Someone like me...

126
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:29,590
just imagines things that haven't happened yet...

127
00:09:29,830 --> 00:09:31,030
and gets anxious.

128
00:09:31,900 --> 00:09:34,270
You're always making your brother worry.

129
00:09:36,130 --> 00:09:37,330
You have a point.

130
00:09:37,790 --> 00:09:39,920
I know it must be tough feeling anxious.

131
00:09:40,700 --> 00:09:41,700
But...

132
00:09:41,740 --> 00:09:43,520
is that really such a bad thing?

133
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:45,910
Huh?

134
00:09:47,020 --> 00:09:48,320
Doesn't it just prove that you...

135
00:09:48,580 --> 00:09:50,550
really, really like my brother, Minato-san?

136
00:09:54,540 --> 00:09:55,540
I see.

137
00:09:56,610 --> 00:09:58,230
When you're feeling anxious,

138
00:09:58,610 --> 00:10:00,350
just remember the happy things he's done for you,

139
00:10:00,730 --> 00:10:02,350
or the fun things you've done together.

140
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:04,470
Think about them one by one.

141
00:10:06,180 --> 00:10:07,230
